---
import { Feature } from "./react/feature";
import { Example } from "./react/example";
/**
 * Feel free to delete this file.
 */
---

<section class="w-full mx-auto p-6 border border-border rounded-xl rich-text">
  <header class="flex gap-1 flex-wrap font-medium text-center">
    <div class="bg-muted rounded-full !text-h6 !leading-8 min-w-8">+</div>
    <h2 class="bg-muted rounded-full !text-h6 !leading-8 !my-0 inline-block px-4 ">neuwaerts</h2>
    <a class="bg-muted rounded-full !text-h6 !leading-8 px-4 !no-underline" href="https://github.com/neuwaerts/astro-boilerplate/releases" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">1.1.0n</a>
  </header>
  <p>This fork extends the capabilities of the Astro Boilerplate with the following features:</p>
  <h3>Added</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><code>.env.example</code> to demonstrate use of environment variables</li>
    <li><code>documentation.md</code> to document project details</li>
  </ul>
  <h3>Changed</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><code>readme.md</code> to match the neuwaerts repository template</li>
    <li><code>.gitignore</code> to match the neuwaerts repository template</li>
    <li><code>meta.astro</code> to use `APP_NAME` for document title</li>
    <li><code>utilities.ts</code> to update typed interfaces</li>
  </ul>
  <Feature flag="development">   
    <hr>
    <h3>Example for the usage of React components</h3>
    <p>The <code>&lt;Example&gt;</code> component gets statically rendered and hydrated. <a href="https://docs.astro.build/de/reference/directives-reference/#clientload">Learn more</a>.</p>
    <Example client:load />
  </Feature>
</section>
